You can add additional color filters to the scanner using the red, green, blue, alpha(transparency) color model. All RGBA values should be between 0-255.
Set the "Alert pixel count range" to the number of pixels you want to color match before being flagged as "Suspicious".

data.name: RichTextBox2.Text
data.value:
Info: The web server allows a means of displaying your server screen shots behind a password protected web page. This gives your server mods and admins the ability to quickly and easily look at suspicious player screen shots that R.A.D.A.R may not have caught during automated scanning.
- Port: The port on which the web server will run. For example: http://192.168.1.100:8088 - Password: The password which is required to view screenshots on the webpage. - Display Limit: The total numbers of screenshots to display per query. - Banner URL or Text: The URL to a .png, .jpg or .gif image which will be displayed at the top of the webpage or just a simple text banner.
Setup: 1 - Configure the computer running R.A.D.A.R with a Static IP address. 2 - Enable the web server in R.A.D.A.R. 3 - Add your selected port as an exception in your Firewall. (TCP) 4 - Forward/NAT your selected port to the Static IP address of your computer on your router's configuration page. 5 - OPTIONAL - Configure a Dynamic DNS address through a service such as DynDNS.org, NoIP.com, etc
Disclosure: There is always a risk of security when deploying publicly accessible services such a web servers. data.name: RichTextBox3.Text
data.value: This tab allows you to find possible alternate accounts of players who have played on your server. This is based upon IP addresses recorded in your PunkBuster log files. To use this feature download your PunkBuster from your server and place them in the "PBLogs" folder. Then click the "Process Log Files" button. Once the log files have been processed you can search for a hero name to find all possible characters that have played from the same IP address.
